The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Sunday, October 27, 2002 				 Indians off to a flier
																								Bled (Slovenia), Oct. 26 (PTI): India started their campaign in the 25th Chess Olympiad on a winning note, with the mens team demolishing Wales 3.5-0.5 and women beating Turkey 2.5-0.5 on Saturday.																								Among the men, GM Abhijit Kunte, R.B. Ramesh and GM Pravin Thipsay won, while P. Harikrishna was held to a draw.																								In the womens, S. Vijayalakshmi and Aarthie Ramaswamy won their matches, while S. Meenakshi was held to a draw.
